&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Peace, inclusion, justice - said Mattarella - are indispensable cornerstones for the sustainable development of each country and every society and I like to emphasize how they are leading principles of the Italian constitutional order". "We make today - it has emphasized in another passage - an additional danger that undermines the relationship of trust with the institutions and between the countries: that of disinformation. On Friday, the World Press Freedom Day admonishes the value of freedom of information for the maintenance of democracy. Themes such as access to information, freedom of expression, protection of privacy, belong, in good law, to the goals included in Objective 16, the subject of this discussion". &nbsp; "With - and in - the United Nations - it has continued - we have to work to restore trust between nations, strengthen international cooperation and weave new networks of understanding and collaboration".
"It is on the basis of this approach - the President has remembered - that Italy unfolds its action, with firm determination to support the tools of dialogue based on that principle of multilateralism that today we see so dramatically questioned by Russian aggression to Ukraine and the consequences of the unsolved Israeli-Palestinian conflict".
