AGI -&nbsp; The graduation ceremony at Columbia, the prestigious University of New York, was cancelled at the center of protests against the war in Gaza.&nbsp; The ceremony should have been held next week, on May 15, but the university said that and will instead organize a series of smaller events.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The demonstrations against the Israeli war against Hamas in Gaza have shaken the US campuses for weeks, causing repression, mass arrest and a White House directive to restore order. Last week, police cleared protesters occupying a Columbia University building and cleared an unauthorized camp on campus lawn.
